d learners whose activity is inseparable from the contexts constructed by the relationships from which they emerge.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCollege teachersxTenure. 0aEducation, HigherxPhilosophy. 0aRelation (Philosophy). 0aUniversities and collegesxFaculty. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Confucianism. 4aEducation : Comparative Education. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aEducation : Philosophy of Education. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848747240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438487472423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438487472/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles